My favourite pet project...<br /><br />Take a look at what FCEUltra does.  It lets the user decide how many scanlines are visible for both NTSC and PAL emulation.  On the TVs/Monitors that I use, the whole NES screen is visible, except for several scanlines at the top.  So, I think giving users the choice is the best solution.<br /><br />No sense in hardcoding your emulator to behave just like a Zenith TV.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=355">ccovell</a> — Mon Jun 26, 2006 7:40 pm</p><hr />
